@vit-zikmund Noticed the layer thing as well. In my case, I build the base image using "regular" Docker on a local machine (as it rarely changes), the overlay/deployment image (which extends from the base) is built automatically by Jenkins using Buildah. Unlike regular Docker and as you have already found out, it only creates a single layer for the entire Dockerfile, which made inspecting the final image a bit tricky.

In my case, the bug really seems to manifest from Buildah itself, as the permissions are entirely fine in the base image built by Docker. It also only started occuring once I upgraded from Debian 12 to 13 which itself has a broken version of Buildah, so I am currently using a self-built version from this repository.

Fwiw, I am using the "bud" (build using Dockerfile) not the regular "build" command.
